<td style=" color:#000000; font-size:12pt; background-color:#FFFFFF; font-family:arial; bLabel:main; bEditID:r3st1;" tEditID="c1r1" locked="0" aEditID="c1r1" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" size="6">British International School</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" size="6">Kuala Lumpur</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" size="4"><i>Charter<font size="4">ed By </font>The British Schools <font size="4">Founda<font size="4">t<font size="4">ion</font></font></font><br></i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><br></div><div style="text-align: left;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Dear {!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.FirstName} {!Contact.LastName},</font></div><div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><div><font face="arial" size="2">After our first full week in school, it is great to see how quickly the children have settled, made new friends and are enjoying the wide range of learning experiences. We now have five classes in each group from year 1 to year 6 and seven in the Early Years Foundation Stage. Although our numbers have grown, we are keen to ensure the school still has a real ‘family’, welcoming atmosphere.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">Partnership with parents is of prime importance and, in addition to the curriculum letters from year teams, we will be hosting a number of Parent Information sessions over the next two weeks.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">Our first one is a <b>‘Welcome Morning’</b> for parents with children in our Early Years Foundation Stage (nursery and reception classes) on Friday 19th September. This will take place straight after drop off in the Primary Music room at 8am and will be an opportunity for you to hear more about the Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS) day-today routines, curriculum and learning environment. After the presentation, parents will be invited to join the children and teaching staff for ‘Pancakes in the Playground’.</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">The following week we have two <b>Parent Information Evenings</b> for children in Key Stage 1 and Key Stage 2. These provide an ideal opportunity to meet myself and the Primary Leadership Team, Year Group Leaders and your child’s class teacher who will be able to explain in more detail the day-to-day routines of school, as well as more in-depth curriculum information. Please make a note in your diary for:</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">Monday 22nd September 2014, 6 – 7pm – Key Stage 2 (Years 3, 4, 5 and 6)</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">Tuesday 23rd September 2014, 6 – 7pm – Key Stage 1 (Years 1 and 2)</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">The children are already following our new ‘Golden Rules’:</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>•<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>Do be gentle</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>•<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>Do be kind</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>•<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>Do work hard</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>•<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>Do look after property</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>•<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>Do listen to people</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>•<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>Do be honest</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">These provide an excellent code of behaviour throughout the primary school and we would encourage parents to support this at home.</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">Mrs. Mackey, our new Deputy Head of Primary, is keen to promote more opportunities for pupil voice and is setting up a new Primary Student Council for children in years 3, 4, 5 and 6, which will be in place by the end of September.</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">We have an enthusiastic team of teachers this year and many creative learning experiences are available for viewing on the Class Portals. Do take a look!</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">I will also be posting this message in Parent Portal; this week will be the last week time I send an email. If you are having difficulty logging into the portal, please contact ICT support at: support@britishschool.edu.my</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">Enjoy the weekend!</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">Kind regards,</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">Debra Birchall</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">Head of Primary</font></div></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><div><div style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><font size="2">British International School Kuala Lumpur</font></span></div></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><i><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600" size="2"><b>World Class Education</b></font></i></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><i><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600"><b><br></b></font></i></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">_________________________________________________________</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">{!User.School_List_Email_Footer__c}</font></div>]]></td>
